# 1. Legal Overview

This document covers every legal and compliance requirement for launching a mobile app business in India. It is organized into actionable sections: business registration, co-founder agreement, data privacy, app store compliance, intellectual property, tax and financial compliance, and ongoing obligations. Each item is prioritized and timestamped so you know what to do now, before launch, and post-launch.

**Important disclaimer:** This document provides guidance based on current Indian laws and regulations as of April 2026. It is not a substitute for professional legal advice. We strongly recommend having a practicing lawyer review all legal documents before execution, particularly the co-founder agreement and privacy policy.

# 2. Business Registration

## 2.1 Entity Structure: LLP vs Private Limited

For two co-founders with no immediate plans to raise external funding, we recommend **LLP (Limited Liability Partnership)** as the starting entity. Here’s why:

| **Factor** | **LLP** | **Private Limited** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Setup Cost** | ₹7,000–15,000 | ₹10,000–20,000 |
| **Annual Compliance** | Low (2 filings/year) | High (8–10 filings/year) |
| **Limited Liability** | Yes | Yes |
| **Taxation** | No Dividend Distribution Tax | DDT applicable |
| **Fundraising** | Harder to raise VC funding | Easy to raise equity funding |
| **Conversion** | Can convert to Pvt Ltd later | N/A |
| **Minimum Partners/Directors** | 2 partners | 2 directors + 2 shareholders |
| **Audit Requirement** | Only if turnover > ₹40L | Mandatory |
| **DPIIT/Startup India** | Eligible | Eligible |
| **Recommendation** | **START HERE** | **Convert when raising funds** |

## 2.2 LLP Registration Steps

| **Step** | **Action** | **Platform/Authority** | **Est. Cost ****&**** Time** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1** | Obtain Digital Signature Certificates (DSC) for both partners | Licensed Certifying Authorities (e.g., eMudhra) | ₹1,000–2,000; 1–2 days |
| **2** | Obtain Designated Partner Identification Number (DPIN) | MCA Portal (mca.gov.in) | Included in FiLLiP; 2–3 days |
| **3** | Reserve LLP Name via RUN-LLP form | MCA Portal | ₹200; 2–5 days |
| **4** | File FiLLiP (Form for incorporation of LLP) | MCA Portal | ₹2,000–5,000; 5–7 days |
| **5** | Receive Certificate of Incorporation + PAN + TAN | MCA/Income Tax auto-allotment | Automatic with Step 4 |
| **6** | Draft and file LLP Agreement (Form 3) | MCA Portal (within 30 days of incorporation) | ₹500 stamp duty + filing |
| **7** | Open business bank account | Any scheduled bank | ₹0; 3–5 days |
| **8** | Register on Startup India Portal for DPIIT recognition | startupindia.gov.in | ₹0; 7–10 days |

**Total estimated cost for LLP registration: ₹5,000–10,000.** Can be done in 10–15 working days. Use a CA or Company Secretary for hassle-free filing, or do it yourself on the MCA portal.

# 3. Co-Founder Agreement

**This is the single most important legal document you will create.** Most startup disputes arise from unclear co-founder agreements. Draft this BEFORE writing any code.

| **Clause** | **What It Should Cover** |
| --- | --- |
| **Equity Split** | Define the ownership percentage (e.g., 50/50). Document the rationale. Include any conditions for adjustment. |
| **Vesting Schedule** | 4-year vesting with 1-year cliff is standard. This protects both partners if one leaves early. Neither partner fully owns their share until vesting completes. |
| **Roles ****&**** Responsibilities** | Clearly define who handles what: business/marketing vs. product/tech (even if AI-assisted). Avoids overlapping authority and accountability gaps. |
| **Decision Making** | Define how decisions are made: unanimous for major (fundraising, pivots, shutting down) vs. domain-specific for daily operations. |
| **Capital Contribution** | Document who is contributing how much (₹75K–1L total). Define if contributions are equal or proportional to equity. |
| **IP Assignment** | All intellectual property created for the business belongs to the LLP, not individuals. This includes code, designs, brand assets, and the AI model. |
| **Compensation ****&**** Salary** | No salary during Year 1 (sweat equity). Define triggers for when salaries begin (e.g., revenue > ₹1L/month). See Document #4. |
| **Exit ****&**** Buyout** | What happens if one co-founder wants to leave? Define buyout terms, notice period (minimum 6 months), and valuation methodology. |
| **Non-Compete** | Prevent partners from starting or joining a competing business for 1–2 years after exit. Must be reasonable in scope and duration. |
| **Dispute Resolution** | Mediation first, then arbitration. Define the seat of arbitration (e.g., Mumbai). Avoids expensive court battles. |
| **Death/Incapacity** | Define what happens to shares if a co-founder dies or becomes incapacitated. Typically: option for surviving partner to buy out from heirs at fair value. |
| **Deadlock Resolution** | If co-founders are 50/50 and disagree on a critical decision, define a tiebreaker mechanism (e.g., external advisor, coin flip for non-critical, mediation for critical). |

**Estimated cost:** ₹5,000–15,000 if drafted with a lawyer. Templates are available online but must be customized. This is NOT the place to cut costs.

# 4. Data Privacy & Protection (DPDP Act 2023)

India’s Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023 (DPDP Act) is the country’s first comprehensive data protection law. The DPDP Rules were notified in November 2025, with full compliance required by **May 2027**. However, building privacy-compliant from day one is both legally prudent and builds user trust.

## 4.1 Data We Collect & Why

| **Data Type** | **Purpose** | **Legal Basis** | **Sensitivity** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Name ****&**** Email** | Account creation, communication | Consent | Standard |
| **Location (City)** | Weather-based meal suggestions | Consent | Standard |
| **Dietary Preferences** | Personalize meal suggestions | Consent | Standard |
| **Health/Diet Goals** | Premium health profiles (pregnancy, recovery) | Explicit Consent | **Sensitive** |
| **Mood Input** | Context-aware AI suggestions | Consent | Standard |
| **Meal History** | AI learning, insights | Consent + Legitimate Use | Standard |
| **Device Info** | App performance, crash reporting | Legitimate Use | Technical |
| **Payment Data** | Subscription billing | Contractual Necessity | **Sensitive** |

## 4.2 DPDP Act Compliance Checklist

| **Requirement** | **Status** | **Action Needed** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Privacy Notice (clear, specific, in plain language) | **Must have before launch** | Draft and display in app + website |
| Consent Collection (free, specific, informed, unconditional) | **Must have before launch** | Build consent UI in onboarding flow |
| Consent Withdrawal (as easy as giving consent) | **Must have before launch** | Add “Withdraw Consent” in app settings |
| Purpose Limitation (use data only for stated purposes) | **Ongoing compliance** | Technical controls in backend |
| Data Minimization (collect only what’s needed) | **Design principle** | Review each data field against purpose |
| Data Retention Policy (delete when no longer needed) | **Must define before launch** | Auto-delete inactive accounts after 2 years |
| Data Breach Notification (72 hours to DPB + users) | **Must have process ready** | Build incident response plan |
| Children’s Data (no tracking/targeting under 18) | **Must have before launch** | Age gate in onboarding; parental consent flow |
| Right to Access (user can request their data) | **Must have before launch** | Build “Download My Data” feature |
| Right to Erasure (user can delete their data) | **Must have before launch** | Build “Delete My Account” feature |
| Data Processor Agreements (with AI API providers) | **Before launch** | Review terms of OpenAI/Gemini/cloud providers |
| Cross-Border Transfer (if using non-India servers) | **Check regulations** | Prefer India-region servers (AWS Mumbai/GCP Mumbai) |

# 5. App Store Compliance

| **Requirement** | **Apple App Store** | **Google Play Store** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Developer Account** | $99/year (~₹8,700) | $25 one-time (~₹2,100) |
| **Privacy Policy URL** | Required (must be accessible) | Required (must be accessible) |
| **Data Safety/Privacy Labels** | App Privacy Nutrition Labels | Data Safety Section |
| **In-App Purchase Rules** | 30% commission on subscriptions | 30% commission (15% after Year 1) |
| **Content Rating** | Must complete questionnaire | Must complete IARC questionnaire |
| **Terms of Service URL** | Required | Required |
| **Ad Disclosure** | Must declare use of ads | Must declare ad SDKs used |
| **Health Claims** | Cannot make unverified health claims | Cannot make unverified health claims |
| **Review Timeline** | 1–3 days (can be longer) | Hours to 7 days |
| **Subscription Guidelines** | Must offer free trial prominently | Must clearly show pricing before purchase |

**Critical:** Both stores charge 30% commission on in-app subscriptions (Google reduces to 15% after the first year). Factor this into pricing. For ₹99/month, you receive ~₹69 after Apple’s cut and ~₹84 after Google’s (Year 2+). Consider offering web-based subscription purchases to avoid the commission.

# 6. Intellectual Property (IP) Protection

| **IP Type** | **What to Protect** | **How** | **Cost ****&**** Timeline** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Trademark** | App name, logo, tagline | File TM application with Indian IP Office | ₹4,500 (per class); 6–12 months |
| **Copyright** | App code, UI designs, recipe content | Automatic (no registration needed, but register for stronger protection) | ₹500–2,000 if registering |
| **Trade Secret** | AI recommendation algorithm, Indian Food Graph data, user behavior models | NDAs with anyone who accesses the data/code. Keep documentation. | ₹0 (just good practices) |
| **Domain Name** | appname.com, appname.in | Register via GoDaddy/Namecheap/Google Domains | ₹800–2,000/year |
| **App Name** | Reserve on App Store & Play Store | Register developer accounts and reserve app name early | Included in dev accounts |

**Priority:** File trademark application immediately once the app name is finalized. This prevents anyone else from registering the same name. Trademark search can be done for free on the IP India website (ipindia.gov.in).

# 7. Tax & Financial Compliance

| **Obligation** | **Details** | **When to Act** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **PAN for LLP** | Allotted automatically with LLP incorporation | Done with registration |
| **GST Registration** | Required when annual turnover exceeds ₹40 Lakhs (goods) or ₹20 Lakhs (services). Register proactively if collecting from inter-state. | Register once revenue starts or before launch if planning inter-state |
| **TDS Compliance** | Deduct TDS on payments to contractors, freelancers, and service providers as applicable | Before making any payments |
| **Income Tax Filing** | LLP must file ITR annually. Tax rate: 30% on net income for LLPs | Annual (due date: October 31) |
| **Tax Audit** | Required if turnover exceeds ₹1 Crore (business) or ₹50 Lakhs (professional services) | Only relevant in Year 2–3 |
| **Startup India Tax Benefit** | 3-year tax holiday (Section 80-IAC) for DPIIT recognized startups. Income tax exemption for 3 consecutive years out of first 10 years. | Apply after DPIIT recognition |
| **Equalisation Levy** | 2% levy on payments to foreign digital service providers (like AI APIs). Already built into pricing by most providers. | Ongoing awareness |
| **Form 11 (Annual Return)** | LLP annual return filed with MCA | Annual (within 60 days of FY end) |
| **Form 8 (Statement of Accounts)** | LLP financial statement filed with MCA | Annual (within 30 days of 6 months from FY end) |
| **Professional Tax** | Applicable in some states (Maharashtra, Karnataka, etc.) | Check state-specific rules |

**Key advantage of DPIIT recognition:** 3-year income tax exemption under Section 80-IAC. At projected Year 2 revenues of ₹1.8 Cr, this saves significant tax. Apply immediately after LLP incorporation.

