# 9. Health & Diet Disclaimer Requirements

Since our app provides meal suggestions including for health conditions (pregnancy, recovery, calorie management), we need clear disclaimers to limit liability:

| **REQUIRED DISCLAIMERS (to be displayed in-app):** • This app provides general meal suggestions for informational purposes only. It does not constitute medical, nutritional, or dietetic advice. • Always consult a qualified healthcare professional, registered dietitian, or nutritionist before making dietary changes, especially if you are pregnant, recovering from surgery, managing a health condition, or on medication. • The app’s AI-generated suggestions are based on general patterns and user inputs. They are not a substitute for professional diagnosis or treatment. • Calorie estimates and nutritional information are approximate. Actual values may vary based on preparation method, ingredients, and portion sizes. • By using this app, you acknowledge that the developers are not liable for any health outcomes resulting from following meal suggestions. |
| --- |

**Placement:** These disclaimers must appear during onboarding (user must accept), in the app’s About/Legal section, and as a subtle note on any health-related meal suggestion.

# 10. Ongoing Compliance Calendar

| **When** | **Obligation** | **Filed With** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Monthly** | GST return filing (GSTR-1, GSTR-3B) if registered | GST Portal |
| **Quarterly** | TDS returns (if applicable) | Income Tax Portal |
| **Within 30 days of FY end** | LLP Form 8 (Statement of Accounts & Solvency) | MCA Portal |
| **Within 60 days of FY end** | LLP Form 11 (Annual Return) | MCA Portal |
| **October 31** | Income Tax Return for LLP | Income Tax Portal |
| **As needed** | Data breach notifications (within 72 hours) | Data Protection Board of India |
| **Annual** | App Store developer account renewal (Apple) | Apple Developer Portal |
| **Annual** | Trademark renewal (every 10 years after registration) | IP India |
| **Annual** | Review and update Privacy Policy and Terms of Service | Internal + App/Website |
| **May 2027** | Full DPDP Act compliance deadline | Data Protection Board |

# 11. Immediate Next Steps

- Draft and sign Co-Founder Agreement (engage a startup lawyer; budget ₹10K–15K)

- Register LLP on MCA portal (or hire a CA/CS for ~₹8K all-inclusive)

- Apply for DPIIT Startup India recognition immediately after LLP is registered

- Finalize app name and file Trademark Application with IP India

- Draft Privacy Policy and Terms of Service (use AI-assisted templates, then get lawyer review)

- Set up financial tracking and open business bank account

- Begin Document #6: Product Requirements Document (PRD)

Total estimated legal costs for all items in this document: **₹25,000–45,000**. This covers LLP registration, co-founder agreement, trademark filing, and template legal documents. Invest in legal foundations now to avoid expensive disputes later.

